  "prompt": "Has anyone survived a plane crash?",
  "response": "Yes, there have been instances where individuals have survived plane crashes. Survival often depends on various factors such as the nature of the crash, the type of aircraft, the location, and the speed of emergency response. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **Juliane Koepcke**: In 1971, Juliane Koepcke survived the crash of LANSA Flight 508 in the Peruvian rainforest. She was the sole survivor and managed to survive for 11 days in the jungle before being rescued.\n\n2. **Cecelia Cichan**: In 1987, Cecelia Cichan was the sole survivor of Northwest Airlines Flight 255, which crashed shortly after takeoff in Detroit. She was only 4 years old at the time.\n\n3. **Bahia Bakari**: In 2009, Bahia Bakari survived the crash of Yemenia Flight 626 off the coast of Comoros. She clung to wreckage in the Indian Ocean for nine hours before being rescued.\n\n4. **Rugby Team (Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571)**: In 1972, members of a Uruguayan rugby team survived a crash in the Andes mountains. They were stranded for 72 days before being rescued, and their story inspired the book and film \"Alive.\"\n\nThese examples demonstrate that survival is possible, though it often involves a combination of luck, resilience, and prompt rescue efforts.",
